genresAdvancedInfo.name: medieval ensemble
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre is characterized by the use of traditional medieval instruments such as lutes, harps, and recorders. The music is often based on historical melodies and chants, and is performed in a chamber music setting with a small group of musicians.
